{image align="right" scale="20" src="HelpImage.png"}

{comment: See the source for more info.}

{define-guitar: G7 base-fret 2 frets 2 4 2 3 2 2 fingers 1 3 1 2 1 1}

{start_of_verse label="Custom Chords"}
You cannot s[E]ee it in the output, [B]but I just
redefined my favorite [G7]G7 Chord!
{comment: Define chords to your liking; the diagram is on the right.}
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_textblock}
If you select a <i>Chord Diagram</i> you can see its known variations and you can add the definition to your song.
{end_of_textblock}

{start_of_textblock label="I'll show my chord:"}
It looks like this:
{chord: G7 base-fret 2 frets 2 4 2 3 2 2 fingers 1 3 1 2 1 1}
{comment: Because I added a <b>chord</b> directive}
{end_of_textblock}

{start_of_textblock label="About me" align="center" flush="left"}
I'm not a musician; I'm not a programmer

I'm just a hobbyist who enjoys both!

Learned programming way back on the `Commodore 64`
but I never made it my work.

<i>If you make your hobby your work it is not your hobby anymore...</i>

So, I didn’t...

I play guitar for more than 20 years; strumming my chords on a beautiful Telecaster. Never got really good at it but I don’t care. I enjoy it!
{end_of_textblock}

{start_of_textblock}
<b>Chord Provider</b> is the result of both hobbies and it serves me well.
- Sometimes I just play the songs in my songbook; sometimes I see that there is something wrong in the book so I solve it.
- Sometimes I just give myself a challenge to add something to the application because its like a crossword challenge
{end_of_textblock}

{comment: <a href="https://github.com/Desbeers/Chord-Provider">Chord Provider on GitHub</a>}

